                "urn": "urn:li:activity:7011321702856998912",
                "followers": 515027,
                "date": "3w",
                "description": "To help keep costs down, Mayo Clinic and UCSF Health are changing the way that providers order anticancer treatments in Epic, and they’re seeing some pretty impressive outcomes.\n\nWith automatic dose rounding (which helps providers reduce the waste of single-dose medications) UCSF saved $2.3 million in 12 months and Mayo saved $7.3 million in 6 months.\n\nBy making preferred biosimilar medications the default choices in cancer treatment plans, Mayo saved $23 million over the course of a year.\n\nMore on their efforts: https://lnkd.in/gp_5tgGA\n\n#healthcare #healthIT #innovation",
