                "urn": "urn:li:activity:7031988996616454144",
                "followers": 525688,
                "date": "1w",
                "description": "“Dugnad,” a type of volunteering, is at the heart of Norwegian culture. It’s a driving force for community, and for our friends at Helse Midt-Norge, it’s a core component of introducing older patients to MyChart. \n\nTo help ensure that MyChart feels accessible to older patients, Helse Midt-Norge built a team of local seniors who volunteered to introduce MyChart to their friends and neighbors. Below is a picture of them at work!\n\nMany volunteers are former IT professionals or healthcare providers, so they understand the benefits of a patient portal and how crucial it is for patients to feel comfortable using one.\n\nCongrats, folks!\n\nRead more: https://lnkd.in/g93fJrPR\n\n#healthcare #healthIT #community",
