                "followers": 533396,
                "date": "4w",
                "description": "Epic Research recently found that higher inpatient postpartum blood pressure readings correlate with higher readmission rates.\n\nIn the study of more than a million birth encounters, patients with BP levels at or above 160/110 shortly before discharge were nearly 3x more likely to be readmitted than patients who had normal BP readings.\n\nTwo authors of the study—Dr. Christopher Alban from Epic and Dr. Kelly Gibson from The MetroHealth System (Cleveland, OH)—sat down with Healthcare IT News to discuss their findings and the potential impact on treatment for new moms. \n\nRead more: https://lnkd.in/gjteJqXJ\n\n#healthcare #healthIT #research",
