                "urn": "urn:li:activity:7042110127885230080",
                "followers": 546103,
                "date": "1mo",
                "description": "Researchers at NYU Langone Health and NYU Grossman School of Medicine found that automated, patient-specific alerts in Epic helped providers more than double new prescriptions of life-saving medications for patients with heart failure.\n\n“We wanted to study this topic because there is a major treatment gap that is a problem for many patients across the United States,” said Amrita Mukhopadhyay, MD, clinical instructor in the department of medicine at NYU Langone Health. “MRAs are medications that can save lives of patients with heart failure. Over two-thirds of patients who could be on an MRA are not prescribed this medication. Closing this treatment gap could save over 20,000 lives per year in the United States.”\n\nRead more: https://lnkd.in/ghAb8Abc\n\n#healthcare #healthIT #hearthealth",
