                "id": 70903646,
                "company_id": 5224619,
                "urn": "urn:li:activity:7029788834259193856",
                "followers": 32887,
                "date": "2d",
                "description": "We are thrilled to announce that Cheshire Oaks has been named the most successful outlet in Europe by business consultancy ecostra, in partnership with the French research institute, Magdus, the European Factory Outlet Centres Observatory.\n \nThis accolade demonstrates significant success for both McArthurGlen and Cheshire Oaks’ owner, LaSalle Investment Management, which acquired the centre last year. \n \nCheshire Oaks was ranked No.1 in the Outlet Centre Performance Report Europe (OCPRE), which is widely considered \"the\" benchmark for the European outlet sector. The report includes a list of the top 20 economically most successful outlets in Europe from the tenant's point of view and features eight McArthurGlen centres in total, more than any other operator. Our Serravalle centre was ranked the most successful in Italy (and third in Europe), with Castel Romano and Noventa di Piave second and third respectively. Our centres in Roermond, Troyes, Parndorf and East Midlands also appeared on the list. \n \nOur ranking and dominance in this year’s OCPRE demonstrates our reputation amongst our valued brand partners, and once again positions McArthurGlen as the market-leading outlet operator.  \n \nMany thanks to all our loyal brand partners for their continued support.  \n\nSusie McCabe Joan Jove Dr. Joachim Will Dr Caroline Lamy John Ralston Kenny Murray Hayden Tucker",
