                "followers": 7229040,
                "date": "12h",
                "description": "\"I'd like to build a career where innovation happens and my work makes a real impact,\" said Luke Kang, Senior Data Scientist at P&G.\n \nIt’s part of the reason Luke chose to work at P&G, he liked that the company had 200 years of innovation history and continually brings “brilliant new products” to market that improve consumers everyday life. His machine leaning and algorithm model has a direct impact on consumers, helping P&G decide what products to deliver to retailers. Luke can see the impact of his work every time he walks into a grocery store. \n \nFrom day one, Luke has owned this project and been able to stay up to date with the always-changing data science industry, thanks to P&G leadership. \"The leadership of the P&G Data Science team understands and recognizes the ongoing up-skill needs,\" Luke said. \"The leadership never stops investing in you.\" #PGInnovation\n \nLearn about data science at P&G more here: https://lnkd.in/d2rHYrn",
