                "description": "Cleaning dishes is the second most hated household chore, according to P&G’s Dish Care Senior Scientist Morgan Eberhard. \n\nThat’s why she’s sharing the secret behind the perfect dishwashing routine and busting some dish-cleaning myths in our Dish Cleaning Myth-Busting series. \n\n“The most common misconception is that you have to pre-wash your dishes before you load them into the dishwasher,” said Eberhard. “In fact, 86% of Americans pre-wash dishes at least once a week. But if you’re using a premium detergent like Cascade Platinum Plus, no pre-wash is needed. Just scrape, load, and you’re done – all while saving time, water, energy, and money in the process.” \n\nEberhard, an 11-year P&G veteran, is dedicated to making dishwashing a more likeable task. Learn more from her on our P&G blog #PGInnovation: https://lnkd.in/eeRcdpQh",
