                "followers": 7295233,
                "date": "1d",
                "description": "“The endgame is to create a technologically-driven business or application, or the technology itself to benefit humans,” says Dr. Fei Fei Li, the co-director of Stanford University’s Human-Centered AI Institute.\n\nCan AI (Artificial Intelligence) be used as a force for good? From the shows that we watch on streaming TV to our healthcare, AI is everywhere. For good or bad, it is here to stay. Dr. Fei Fei Li, a former vice president at Google, former chief scientist of the AI Machine Learning Group at Google Cloud, and former director of Stanford University’s AI lab, shared in an interview at P&G Signal 2021, “We want this technology to bring positive potential and not the negativity that would impact individuals, communities and people around the world.” Read more about how “human-centered AI” can benefit individuals, as well as businesses: https://lnkd.in/epmvdW2Q",
