                "urn": "urn:li:activity:7027326798669496320",
                "followers": 7295233,
                "date": "2d",
                "description": "Through #PGInnovation and inclusive design, we’re enabling consumers to live more sustainably. Learn more from The Wall Street Journal.\n\n“Consumers would go right to, ‘Your packaging is so plastic’, and then usually in the next breath they would say, ‘And it’s so hard to open’,” said Kara Buckley, head of global grooming communications at Procter & Gamble, told Katie Deighton of the Wall Street Journal. \n\nIn 2021, our Gillette team began the switch from selling our razors in plastic blister packs and trays to delivering them in a pulp tray and cardboard packaging. Today, around 80% of our refillable razors globally are now sold in the new packaging. \n\nhttps://lnkd.in/gQCSg3zD",
