                "date": "1d",
                "description": "#MustWatch: We partnered with CENTRAL CITY PRODUCTIONS to present Black History Honors, a four-part docuseries honoring the heroes of the Underground Railroad, part of our ongoing commitment to accurately portray the vastness, resilience, beauty, and joy of the Black experience. \n\nOur team gathered with GRAMMY Award-winner Mali Music and MARC MORIAL, president of the National Urban League, among other dignitaries and friends at the National Underground Railroad Freedom Center, celebrating the premier of the new annual Black History Month television series. Learn more about the series: https://lnkd.in/ebTtxzt6 \n\nAt P&G, we understand that reaching underrepresented audiences with accurate, authentic stories helps remove bias and inspire inclusion. That’s why our Black Owned and Operated Media team leads the industry with equitable actions to #WidenTheScreen so we can widen our view. Learn more about our commitments: https://lnkd.in/ewNDj4UT  #BlackHistoryMonth #BlackHistory #PGStudios",
