                "reshared_post_author_url": "https://uk.linkedin.com/in/samlatif",
                "reshared_post_author_headline": "Company Accessibility Leader at Procter & Gamble",
                "reshared_post_description": "So happy Procter & Gamble received PAC Global Best of Show award for Ariel’s ECOCLIC® box this week at the PAC Global Summit in New York. \n\nAriel’s ECOCLIC® box stood out thanks to the combination of safe, sustainable and inclusive design. Our box is certified for child safety and at the same time inclusively designed to be delightful for adults. The opening experience is incredible for everyone, and especially for people with hand-dexterity challenges. \n\nFor blind and low vision people, we introduced a new tactile symbol that helps identify the product through touch as a laundry detergent. ECOCLIC® also features the NaviLens code, which can be scanned with the phone to locate the product on the shelf and learn more about it. So well deserved for the entire Ariel team behind this #DisabilityConfident invention! \n  \nI also had the privilege to participate in the opening panel session with Pete Matthews and Bethany Foor from Kellogg’s and Marc Powell PLY from RNIB, where we shared our respective companies’ journey on integrating accessibility into our company brand strategy. \n\nThank you Jim Downham and the entire PAC team! It was an awesome and superbly organized event, and I just loved the thoughtful audio description of each of the winning videos, which was definitely appreciated by all 3 of us blind and low vision attendees.",
