                "followers": 7310243,
                "date": "4d",
                "description": "For #NationalInventorsDay we’re remembering when P&G hired a young Thomas Edison who applied for a job — as a mechanic.\n \nDuring his time, Edison met with P&G co-founder James N. Gamble to advise him to invest in a dedicated telegraph line to connect the Main Office to the plant on Central Avenue, two miles away. Up to this point, P&G used couriers to shuttle orders back and forth. Edison taught employees how to operate the telegraph and remarked that Gamble was especially adept and skilled.\n \nSerendipitous strokes of genius and passion-fueled ideas launched iconic brands and defined us as a company. We celebrate the spirit of our innovators every day. \n\nLearn more here: https://lnkd.in/esUu5_rJ #PGInnovation #PGHeritage #FlashbackFriday",
