                "description": "In 1924, we began recruiting female college graduates to serve as Field Investigators for our new Market Research Department. These young women traveled the country going door-to-door asking consumers what they thought of our products and advertisements.  \n\nOur diverse workforce carries that same spirit of curiosity today to develop our product innovations, finding inspiration in people — their needs, values, desires and passions — to solve consumers’ everyday problems. \n\nFollow our #WomensHistoryMonth blog series to learn more about some of the P&G women behind our product innovations: https://lnkd.in/ga9muQk2  \n\n#PGHeritage #WeSeeEqual #PGInnovation",
