                "urn": "urn:li:activity:7037119395218825217",
                "followers": 7343669,
                "date": "2d",
                "description": "The ongoing partnership to support the LGBTQ+ community is grounded in our mission to create a company and world where equality and inclusion exists for all.\n \nOn February 22, Procter & Gamble Australia and New Zealand, Sydney WorldPride and Sydney Gay and Lesbian Mardi Gras hosted a panel unpacking the importance of LGBTQ+ visibility in advertising, media, and the world, followed by a private screening of award-winning documentary short film CODED: The Hidden Love of J.C. Leyendecker, produced by P&G and Imagine Entertainment & Television. \n \nThe film explores early representation of LGBTQ+ communities through arts and advertising. Brent Miller, CODED Executive Producer and P&G Senior Director for Global LGBTQ+ Equality, reflects, “despite Leyendecker’s story being one of 100 years ago, it is still of great relevance today. It has created a powerful conversation about the role of advertising and the responsibility corporations have to make equitable choices regarding the ways we represent the humanity of people. We never made this film to win awards, we made it to tell a story and move important issues forward.”\n \nLearn more about CODED and our commitment to visibility by visiting the link here: https://lnkd.in/eiqEuUXK\n \n#UniqueAndUnited",
