                "date": "1d",
                "description": "“I transitioned from being an African orphan from an under-privileged background in Zimbabwe to winning the Black British Business Awards.”\n \nHear how Prince Chakanyuka, eCommerce Customer Supply Chain Manager, has been able to grow and learn while making an impact at P&G. Through his work with the Belong affinity group - a P&G network helping to build a space to celebrate people from different backgrounds and cultures and ensure everyone is able to bring their authentic selves to work – Prince hopes to empower others and show how everyone can thrive at P&G.\n \nAt P&G, we believe that P&G + Me = Mutual Success. No two P&G experiences or people are the same. And how the formula for success looks and feels is made up of something different for each of us.\n\nLearn why P&G is a #GreatPlaceToWork: https://lnkd.in/ggNbhGny \n \n #PGandMe",
