                "company_id": 10798424,
                "urn": "urn:li:activity:7057308053917859840",
                "followers": 7439930,
                "date": "4d",
                "description": "Bounty paper towels are more durable than before thanks to brand-new technology, making them even stronger. \n\nBounty Senior Scientist Gregg Weaver puts new Bounty paper towels to the test with 10 pounds worth of nuts and bolts weighted on top of just one sheet. On top of the 10 pounds of weight, Weaver then adds green-colored water.  \n\n“Bounty’s new proprietary microstructure is larger than our previous design and built to hold up under pressure. You may not see it, but you can feel the difference,” said Weaver. \n\nNew Bounty is hitting store shelves this Spring, just in time for Spring cleaning! Learn more about this #PGInnovation: https://lnkd.in/gY6-T-2M",
