                "urn": "urn:li:activity:7056945368957153281",
                "followers": 7439930,
                "date": "5d",
                "description": "Bounty paper towels are more absorbent than before, but don’t take our word for it.\n\nBounty Senior Scientist Gregg Weaver puts it to the test in this demo using water with green dye in it to show how Bounty absorbs moisture.\n\n“The new technology creates dedicated absorbance zones, which pump and direct liquid more evenly through the sheet, trapping and locking the mess in both directions. It also has dedicated strong and flexible zones making it cloth-like,” explained Weaver.\n\nTo learn more about the technology in new Bounty: https://lnkd.in/gY6-T-2M",
